<td colspan="2" class="summary" style="text-align:center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; background-color: lightsteelblue">Mountain Meadows massacre</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a href="/wiki/File:MMM-Harpersw8-13-1859.jpg" class="image" title="MMM-Harpersw8-13-1859.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/01/MMM-Harpersw8-13-1859.jpg/250px-MMM-Harpersw8-13-1859.jpg" width="250" height="165" border="0" /></a><br />
<span style="">The cover of the August 13, 1859 issue of <i><a href="/wiki/Harper%27s_Weekly" title="Harper's Weekly">Harper's Weekly</a></i> illustrating the killing field as described by Brevet Major Carleton "one too horrible and sickening for language to describe. Human skeletons, disjointed bones, ghastly skulls and the hair of women were scattered in frightful profusion over a distance of two miles." "the remains were not buried at all until after they had been dismembered by the wolves and the flesh stripped from the bones, and then only such bones were buried as lay scattered along nearest the road".</span></td>
</tr>
